    <div class="title">How old is Providence?</div>
    <div class="explanation">
      <p><a href="https://chris.sarl/how-old-is-providence/">How old is Providence?</a> is a map of parcels in Providence, stylized by the year of last building construction. All of the data comes from <a href="https://pvdgis.maps.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=1700e1cf7228491d962973edc9924484" rel="external">the City&rsquo;s GIS Portal.</a> This visualization was inspired by Kyril Negoda&rsquo;s <a href="https://spatialthinking.tumblr.com/post/160598058069/minneapolis-building-age-zoomable-version-mapping" rel="external">How old is Minneapolis?</a></p>
      <p>Hovering on a parcel reveals the year, and clicking on it will open the relevant entry in <a href="https://gis.vgsi.com/providenceri/" rel="external">Vision.</a></p>
