    <div class="title">GBFS Viewer</div>
    <div class="explanation">
      <p><a href="http://chris-sarli.github.io/GBFS-Viewer/">GBFS Viewer</a> is a very simple tool that uses <a href="https://github.com/NABSA/gbfs" target="_blank">GBFS</a> feeds to provide a realtime map of multiple scooter- and
        bike-share systems.
        The tool is adaptable to any City and feed provider (as long as their
        GBFS follows the <a href="https://github.com/NABSA/gbfs/blob/master/gbfs.md" target="_blank">official specification</a>), but this instance has been created for
        operators in Providence, RI.</p>
      <p>The tool also counts vehicles per geographic zone specified for <a href="https://www.providenceri.gov/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/PTD-Regulations-Sept-1-2019.pdf" target="_blank">regulatory distribution requirements.</a></p>
